            "title": "UnitedHealth Non-GAAP EPS of $2.11 in-line, revenue of $113.21B misses by $520M",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>UnitedHealth <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20376719-unitedhealth-group-reports-2025-results-and-issues-2026-outlook\">press release</a> (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/UNH\" title=\"UnitedHealth Group Incorporated\">UNH</a></span>): Q4 Non-GAAP EPS of $2.11 in-line.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $113.21B (+12.3% Y/Y) <span> misses by $520M</span>.</li>\n<li>Full Year 2026 Revenue Outlook Greater Than $439.0 Billion vs $455.98B consensus; Earnings Outlook Greater Than $17.10 Per Share; Adjusted Earnings Greater Than $17.75 Per Share vs $17.76 consensus</li>\n<li>\n<p data-eci=\"true\">2025 Key Performance Metrics</p>\n<ul>\n<li>UnitedHealthcare, which served 49.8 million consumers in 2025, grew revenues 16% to $344.9 billion.</li>\n<li>Optum expanded revenues 7% to $270.6 billion and supported more than 123 million consumers across its businesses.</li>\n<li>The reported medical care ratio of 89.1% included a 20 basis point negative impact from loss contracts included in the charge, resulting in an adjusted medical care ratio of 88.9%, or an increase of 340 basis points year-over-year.</li>\n<li>The operating cost ratio of 13.3% included a negative 40 basis points impact from the one-time charge, resulting in an adjusted operating cost ratio of 12.9%, which was flat year-over-year.</li>\n<li> </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Shares <span>-9%</span> PM.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
